---
// Candle Master - Terms of Service Page
const appName = 'Candle Master';
const appUrl = 'https://app.candlemaster.app';
const siteUrl = 'https://candlemaster.app';
const contactEmail = 'pathofmeow.dev@gmail.com';
const lastUpdated = 'February 10, 2026';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/favicon-32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="32x32" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

    <!-- SEO Meta Tags -->
    <title>Terms of Service — {appName}</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Terms of Service for Candle Master trading simulator game." />

    <!-- Canonical -->
    <link rel="canonical" href={`${siteUrl}/terms`} />

    <!-- Geist Font -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://cdn.vercel.com" crossorigin />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.vercel.com/geist/font/sans/geist-sans.css" />

    <!-- Theme CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/theme.css" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <main class="legal-page">
      <div class="legal-container">
        <!-- Back to Home -->
        <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Home</a>

        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

        <section>
          <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing or using {appName} ("the Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of
            Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p>
            {appName} is a trading simulator game designed for educational purposes. The Service allows
            users to practice stock trading using historical market data in a simulated environment.
          </p>
          <p><strong>Important:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>{appName} is NOT a financial advisor, broker, or investment platform.</li>
            <li>No real money is traded within the game.</li>
            <li>Historical stock data is used for educational simulation only.</li>
            <li>Past performance in the simulator does not indicate future real-world results.</li>
            <li>We do not provide investment advice or recommendations.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. User Accounts</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>You may sign in using your Google account through Firebase Authentication.</li>
            <li>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account.</li>
            <li>You must provide accurate information when creating your account.</li>
            <li>One account per person. Sharing accounts is not permitted.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Subscriptions and Payments</h2>

          <h3>4.1 Free and PRO Plans</h3>
          <p>
            {appName} offers a free tier with limited features and a PRO subscription with expanded
            access. Current pricing and feature details are available within the app and on our website.
          </p>

          <h3>4.2 Payment Processing</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Web (PWA):</strong> Payments are processed by Stripe. By purchasing a subscription, you also agree to <a href="https://stripe.com/legal" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stripe's Terms of Service</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>iOS:</strong> Payments are processed through Apple's In-App Purchase system and are subject to <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple's Terms</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>Android:</strong> Payments are processed through Google Play Billing and are subject to <a href="https://play.google.com/about/play-terms/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Play's Terms</a>.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>4.3 Monthly Subscriptions</h3>
          <p>
            Monthly subscriptions renew automatically each billing cycle until cancelled. You may
            cancel at any time. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period.
          </p>

          <h3>4.4 Lifetime Plans</h3>
          <p>
            Lifetime plans provide permanent access to PRO features with a one-time payment.
            Lifetime access is tied to your account and is non-transferable.
          </p>

          <h3>4.5 Refunds</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Web (Stripe):</strong> Refund requests can be made within 7 days of purchase by contacting us at <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>iOS / Android:</strong> Refunds are handled by Apple or Google respectively, per their refund policies.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any part of the Service</li>
            <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Service or related systems</li>
            <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service</li>
            <li>Use automated tools or bots to interact with the Service</li>
            <li>Share or redistribute PRO content without authorization</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            All content, features, and functionality of the Service — including but not limited to
            design, graphics, characters, sounds, and code — are owned by {appName} and are protected
            by copyright and intellectual property laws.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Disclaimer of Financial Advice</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>The Service is for educational and entertainment purposes only.</strong> Nothing
            in {appName} constitutes financial advice, investment advice, trading advice, or any other
            sort of advice. You should not treat any of the content as such. We do not recommend that
            any financial instrument should be bought, sold, or held by you. Trading and investing in
            financial markets involves risk. Always do your own research and consult with a qualified
            financial advisor before making investment decisions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, {appName} shall not be liable for any indirect,
            incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including but not limited to
            loss of profits, data, or other intangible losses resulting from your use of the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Service Availability</h2>
          <p>
            We strive to maintain the Service but do not guarantee uninterrupted availability. We
            reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue the Service at any time with
            reasonable notice.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the Service after changes
            constitutes acceptance of the new Terms. We will notify users of material changes via
            the app or email.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us at:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Email: <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a></li>
            <li>Website: <a href={siteUrl}>{siteUrl}</a></li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: var(--bg-primary);
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
  }

  .legal-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding: 0;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-default);
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  ul {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-page {
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem 3rem;
    }
  }
</style>
